beer.beer_description: Don't get us wrong, we like our big heavy Double and Triple IPA's. But sometimes, sometimes, we want to have the staying power to sit around the campfire long into the evening and regale our mates with stories they've probably heard a hundred times before. For these occasions, we decided to make the math easy for everyone. One Standard Drink is just that, in a 440mL format can, dry hopped at with some of our favourites - Simcoe, Vic Secret, Riwaka (from our mates at Eggers Farm in NZ), and Sabro; giving you a well rounded, punchy piney, tropical beverage letting you kick back rather then fall back. Cheers to the making it to the wee hours!

items.badge_description: Steinholding is no easy sport. According to the U.S. Steinholding Association (USSA) in their years of training, competing, judging, and organizing steinholding competitions theyve seen incredible examples of athleticism and determination. The USSA has made it their goal to share these experiences around the world. With the 186th Oktoberfest kicking off last Thursday its time to dust off your steins and hoist one as high as you can for as long as you can. And then afterwards treat yourself to the beer inside! #steinsup
